						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in the compound of the Kēśavasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1650, Kīlaka, Jyēshṭa śu. 5,</hi> corresponding to 1728 A.D., June 1, Saturday.</p>						

						<p>It states the construction of a <hi rend="italic">Dharma-maṇḍapam</hi> by Huḍēdārs. It also refers to <hi rend="italic">gōmājiśēva</hi> (service instituted by gōmāji) in the same year, but on Śu. 10.</p>						

						</summary>
